The value of colombian exports other thancoffee rose 55 pct in january compared with the same periodlast year, apparently setting a trend for the trade balance in1987, government statistics institute figures show.    They amounted to 180.8 mln dlrs fob compared with 147.5 mlndlrs for coffee, a drop of 42 pct from last year.    The trade balance registered a 35 mln dlr surplus, comparedwith a 56 mln dlr surplus in january 1986.    The national planning department forecast that in 1987coffee, colombia's traditional major export, will account foronly one-third of total exports, or about 1.5 billion dlrs. Reuter&#3;